availability of Internet-enabled consumer-grade power meters.
While many dimensions of the problem have been well-studied
over the past 25 years, we argue that prior work has placed
too much emphasis on incremental improvements in accuracy
and not enough on designing novel NILM applications. As a
result, the basic NILM problem and its primary application—
a simple appliance-level breakdown of home energy usage—has
remained unchanged since its inception. We believe a renewed
focus on NILM applications could help steer future research in
novel directions by exposing new problem variants, data analysis
techniques, and evaluation metrics. In this paper, we summarize
our own application-centric research agenda, which focuses on
online applications that generate results in real time as smart
meters produce data. As we discuss, our focus on applications has
