* They assume the distributions of energy consumption are normally distributed but give no evidence to support this assumption (they don't even mention it).  Although apparently normality isn't essential, especially if N is big: http://thestatsgeek.com/2013/09/28/the-t-test-and-robustness-to-non-normality/
